      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "url": "https://app.telegasend.ru"
        },
        "description": "This API allows users to create, manage, and track mailing lists within the Telegram platform. It provides endpoints to create new mailings, check their status, and cancel existing mailings.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://app.telegasend.ru/api/v1"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Telegram Mailing Service",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Create, manage, and track mailing campaigns sent through Telegram bots",
        "homepage": "https://app.telegasend.ru",
        "docs_url": "https://freepublicapis.com/telegram-mailing-service",
        "about_md": "The Telegram Mailing Service API is provided by [TelegaSend](https://app.telegasend.ru), a service that lets developers run bulk-messaging campaigns to Telegram users through a bot. Requests are made against `https://app.telegasend.ru/api/v1` and authenticated with a Telegram `bot_token` supplied in the request body.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- Launch a new mailing with a bot token, message text, optional schedule, development-mode flag, and a recipient list supplied via file URL (`POST /api/v1/mailing`).\n- Look up the current delivery status of a previously created mailing by its identifier (`GET /api/v1/mailing/{id}`).\n- A per-mailing recipient cap of 1,000.\n\nOperational notes: CORS is disabled, so the API is intended for server-side use rather than direct browser calls. Community monitoring on FreePublicAPIs reports ~700ms average response times and 100% reliability over a recent 30-day window. Licence terms are not published on the catalogue page — consult TelegaSend directly before relying on the service.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "mailing": "A Telegram mailing campaign — created with `POST /api/v1/mailing` (bot token, message, schedule, recipient file URL) and inspected with `GET /api/v1/mailing/{id}` for delivery status."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
